This paper discusses the security and privacy practices of websites, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes improvements to website ranking systems, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or data mining (cs.DL). The manipulation of website rankings could also be considered a form of cybercrime (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the representativeness of website rankings, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI).
